Name: Tallinn
Description: Tallinn is Estonia's capital and largest city. On the shore of the Gulf of Finland, it is a city of over 400,000 inhabitants. It is home to a third of the country's population, and is also the capital of Harju County in Northern Estonia.

Name: Tartu
Description: Tartu (formerly known as Dorpat or Yuryev) is the second largest city in Estonia with a population of 100,000.

Name: Narva
Description: Narva is the easternmost city in Estonia, at the Russian border.

Name: Pärnu
Description: Pärnu is a resort seaside city (and Estonia's summer capital) with a small harbour in south-western Estonia.

Name: Rakvere
Description: Rakvere (Tarbapea in ancient Estonian, Weisenberg in German, Rakowor in Russian) is Estonia’s fifth largest city and situated the northern part of the country, 20 km south of the Gulf of Finland and approximately 100 km east of Tallinn, Estonia.

Name: Haapsalu
Description: Haapsalu is a major seaside resort town on the west coast of Estonia, approximately 100 km south-west of Tallinn.

Name: Viljandi
Description: Viljandi is an ancient hilly city in the South of Estonia.

Name: Kuressaare
Description: Kuressaare is the capital of Saaremaa, the largest of Estonia's islands.

Name: Valga
Description: Valga is a town in southern Estonia, on the border with Latvia. Valga and Valka in Latvia are actually one town. Valga is bigger with around 15,000 inhabitants.

Name: Lahemaa National Park
Description: Lahemaa National Park (Estonian: Lahemaa rahvuspark) is a national park in North Estonia.

Name: Soomaa National Park
Description: Soomaa National Park [1] is in Viljandimaa and Pärnumaa of Estonia. With 390 km², it's the second largest national park in Estonia.

Name: Matsalu National Park
Description: Matsalu National Park is in Läänemaa county, western Estonia.

Name: Vilsandi National Park
Description: Vilsandi National Park is on and outside Saaremaa, Estonia's largest island. The park includes the island of Vilsandi, 160 other islands and islets, parts of Western Saaremaa and the Harilaid peninsula.

Name: Karula National Park
Description: Karula National Park [dead link] is in Valgamaa of Estonia.

Name: Otepää
Description: Otepää is a small town with 2,000 inhabitants set in the hills of south Estonia, approximately 50 km north from Tartu.

Name: Saaremaa
Description: Saaremaa is the largest Estonian island, situated on the west coast of Estonia. The capital (and only city) in Saaremaa is Kuressaare.

Name: Hiiumaa
Description: Hiiumaa is the second biggest island in Estonia. The Swedish and German name of the island is Dagö.

Name: Kihnu
Description: Kihnu is the largest island in the Gulf of Riga and one of the smallest municipalities in Estonia.

Name: Muhu
Description: Muhu is the third largest island in Estonia, although it is fairly small at 198 square kilometres. It's located between the mainland and Saaremaa Island.

Name: Ruhnu
Description: Ruhnu is a small island in Estonia, isolated from the rest of the country in the Gulf of Riga. The island is called Runö in Swedish.

Name: Vormsi
Description: Vormsi is a small island in Estonia.
